WEBVTT

00:05.266 --> 00:08.965
Previously
onBlood & Treasure...DANNY: The Khan is after money.

00:09.009 --> 00:10.836
This isn't about terror.

00:10.880 --> 00:12.142
This is a heist.

00:12.186 --> 00:13.404
DANNY:
This whole time,

00:13.448 --> 00:14.840
she's needed one thing

00:14.884 --> 00:16.538
to pull off this heist.The Spirit Banner

00:16.581 --> 00:18.235
of Genghis Khan.

00:18.279 --> 00:19.628
CHAN: Millions of SWIFT
bank deposits locked

00:19.671 --> 00:21.630
inside the Banner.So you mean

00:21.673 --> 00:23.675
$1.5 trillion is trapped

00:23.719 --> 00:25.155
inside the Soul of Genghis Khan.

00:25.199 --> 00:27.070
DANNY:
We need to get that banner.

00:27.114 --> 00:28.463
Hong Kong Police!
Put down your weapons!

00:28.506 --> 00:30.508
Did you call the cops?I thought you did.

00:30.552 --> 00:31.814
Actually I called them.

00:31.857 --> 00:33.076
On your knees, Khan!

00:33.120 --> 00:35.731
I am not the Khan, okay?

00:35.774 --> 00:37.167
Wait, he's actually
telling the truth.

00:37.211 --> 00:39.561
Yeah, I've been on your side
this whole time.

00:39.604 --> 00:42.172
VIOLET:
We found where they're taking
Simon Hardwick and my Banner.

00:42.216 --> 00:44.827
I want it back.

00:44.870 --> 00:46.307
SHAW:
Remember that attack

00:46.350 --> 00:48.309
on the Russian military base?

00:48.352 --> 00:50.528
Violet definitely stole a nuke.

00:50.572 --> 00:52.530
Violet's going after that Banner
with everything she has.

00:52.574 --> 00:55.620
DANNY:
She'll blow up Hong Kong
to cover her tracks.

00:56.621 --> 00:58.667
♪

01:06.153 --> 01:08.198
[crowd clamoring]

01:11.158 --> 01:12.681
Hey.
[panting]

01:12.724 --> 01:14.465
Are you okay?Sorry I'm late.

01:14.509 --> 01:16.467
I almost got run over by,
like, three different dragons.

01:16.511 --> 01:19.340
Pretend dragons, but still...

01:19.383 --> 01:21.037
it was scary.

01:21.081 --> 01:22.256
Danny still waiting to talk
to the superintendent?

01:22.299 --> 01:24.258
Yep, 20 minutes and counting.

01:24.301 --> 01:25.737
FATHER CHUCK: Does the
superintendent know

01:25.781 --> 01:27.130
that there's a nuclear bomb...?

01:27.174 --> 01:28.349
Hey, hey, hey!
We don't want to startHey!

01:28.392 --> 01:29.567
a panic shouting
that out now.

01:29.611 --> 01:30.960
You know what, can we just

01:31.003 --> 01:32.135
put the bomb on a boat

01:32.179 --> 01:33.876
and shove it out
into the harbor?

01:33.919 --> 01:35.573
Can't. It's rigged to detonate
if anyone tries to move it.

01:35.617 --> 01:37.184
Awesome.

01:37.227 --> 01:38.924
Look, Violet can't set off
the nuke as long

01:38.968 --> 01:40.752
as the Banner's here with
the trillion dollars inside it

01:40.796 --> 01:43.103
or this was all for nothing.Well, not allfor nothing.

01:43.146 --> 01:45.235
Based on what she told me
last time I was here,

01:45.279 --> 01:46.889
she hates Hong Kong.

01:46.932 --> 01:48.499
I don't think the bomb is
only to cover her tracks.

01:48.543 --> 01:49.892
She wants to blow this place up.

01:49.935 --> 01:51.285
Over our dead bodies.

01:51.328 --> 01:52.938
Yeah, that's what I'm afraid of.Yeah, me, too.

01:52.982 --> 01:54.723
Hey.
What's going on?

01:54.766 --> 01:56.246
Superintendent
is coming now.

01:56.290 --> 01:57.639
He sure took his bloody time.

01:57.682 --> 01:59.380
They think Simon is
the Great Khan,

01:59.423 --> 02:01.556
so we're caught up
in this giant ball of red tape,

02:01.599 --> 02:03.862
which will get sorted out,
but in the meantime,

02:03.906 --> 02:05.560
we need to make sure
the bomb is neutralized

02:05.603 --> 02:07.605
and this place is secured.

02:07.649 --> 02:09.651
We've got to grab the Banner
and we've got to go.

02:09.694 --> 02:10.869
Even if we could,
we're safer in here

02:10.913 --> 02:12.132
than out there with the Banner,

02:12.175 --> 02:13.611
where every criminal
in Asia's

02:13.655 --> 02:15.787
gonna be looking for us.I know I've said this

02:15.831 --> 02:17.528
once before,
but I'm gonna try one more time.

02:17.572 --> 02:19.922
We should destroy the Banner
and the money inside it.

02:19.965 --> 02:21.663
Dangerous as she is now,
if she gets it,

02:21.706 --> 02:23.143
how much more dangerous is she?

02:23.186 --> 02:25.057
The money is power.

02:25.101 --> 02:26.972
The-the Banner is like
the One Ring and we need to send

02:27.016 --> 02:28.844
that sucker into Mount Doom
before Lady Sauron

02:28.887 --> 02:30.019
takes over Middle Earth.

02:30.062 --> 02:31.455
Lord of the Rings.

02:31.499 --> 02:34.110
Solid analogy.Thanks, buddy.

02:34.154 --> 02:35.372
Yeah, well done.

02:35.416 --> 02:37.026
Okay, okay, focus, nerds.

02:37.069 --> 02:38.636
We can't destroy the Banner.

02:38.680 --> 02:40.334
Violet will lose her mind.Well, let her.

02:40.377 --> 02:41.944
We all know her game now.

02:41.987 --> 02:43.206
Her horde, they're
just a bunch of mercenaries,

02:43.250 --> 02:44.294
only in it for money.

02:44.338 --> 02:45.687
That makes them weak.

02:45.730 --> 02:47.036
Once the money is gone,

02:47.079 --> 02:48.864
there goes all her power.

02:48.907 --> 02:50.561
I fell asleep
during Lord of the Rings.

02:50.605 --> 02:52.433
Did the bad guys have
a nuclear bomb?

02:52.476 --> 02:55.262
Look, the Banner and the money
in it isn't ours to destroy.

02:56.393 --> 02:58.787
Now this place...
is a fortress.

02:58.830 --> 03:00.876
Complete with its own army.

03:00.919 --> 03:03.008
So you're counting on them
to protect us?

03:03.052 --> 03:04.532
Whatever happened
to "you're

03:04.575 --> 03:06.229
better off not putting
your faith in anyone"?

03:06.273 --> 03:09.058
TSANG: Mr. McNamara,
this way, please.

03:09.101 --> 03:11.147
Everything is
under control.

03:11.191 --> 03:13.236
Chinese Intelligence will take
Simon Hardwick into custody

03:13.280 --> 03:15.238
and transfer him
to the mainland.

03:15.282 --> 03:17.153
The threat is over.

03:17.197 --> 03:20.069
He was caught red-handed
trying to take the Banner

03:20.112 --> 03:22.289
and now...

03:22.332 --> 03:23.942
the Khan is in jail.

03:23.986 --> 03:26.467
You'll be treated fairly.HARDWICK: I am the victim.

03:26.510 --> 03:28.817
As hard as that is
to believe me, I'm the victim.

03:28.860 --> 03:31.472
I was kidnapped at gunpoint,
I was shot.

03:31.515 --> 03:34.039
I was branded
and I was forced to work

03:34.083 --> 03:37.217
for that maniac against my will
or she'd have executed me.

03:38.914 --> 03:42.004
Lucky part is I actually know
the final part of her plan.

03:42.047 --> 03:43.962
And I want to help.

03:44.006 --> 03:47.444
Assuming we can cut a deal
before she kills us all.

03:47.488 --> 03:50.273
Look, all due respect,
Superintendent, he's right.

03:50.317 --> 03:52.057
You're saying that Simon
Hardwick is totally innocent?

03:52.101 --> 03:53.842
No, I'm saying
he's not the Khan.

03:53.885 --> 03:55.539
The real Khan is
on the way.

03:55.583 --> 03:57.759
Right now.
To get the Banner.

03:57.802 --> 04:00.152
And she's planted
a nuclear bomb under the city.

04:00.196 --> 04:02.024
What?
SHAW:
I can show you where.

04:02.067 --> 04:04.026
But we got to get somebody
defusing it, pronto.

04:04.069 --> 04:05.984
LEXI:
If she gets the Banner
and escapes,

04:06.028 --> 04:07.725
she will detonate that nuke

04:07.769 --> 04:09.510
to cover her tracks.

04:09.553 --> 04:12.774
HARDWICK:
This has nothing to do with me.

04:12.817 --> 04:16.081
This entire city is
in great danger.

04:16.125 --> 04:19.781
You need to speak to my friends
Danny McNamara and Lexi Vaziri.

04:19.824 --> 04:22.305
You're his... friends?

04:22.349 --> 04:23.567
No, not exactly.No, not at all.

04:23.611 --> 04:25.308
[crashing, rumbling]

04:25.352 --> 04:27.528
What was that?

04:31.140 --> 04:32.184
It's got to be her.

04:35.623 --> 04:37.886
Phone's not getting any signal.

04:37.929 --> 04:39.583
She blacked out
all of Hong Kong.

04:39.627 --> 04:42.020
We're not gonna be able
to call for backup.

04:42.064 --> 04:44.806
Superintendent, get your men
ready for an attack.

04:44.849 --> 04:46.721
LEXI:
No, it's too late.

04:48.810 --> 04:50.855
♪

04:56.644 --> 04:58.689
She's already here.

04:58.733 --> 05:00.778
♪

05:04.869 --> 05:06.915
♪

05:22.800 --> 05:24.672
♪

05:44.300 --> 05:45.432
[beeps]

05:54.441 --> 05:56.617
We are ready for
whatever's coming.

05:56.660 --> 05:58.488
I have every available
officer guarding the front

05:58.532 --> 06:00.272
and back entrances.

06:00.316 --> 06:02.013
The only ways in.FATHER CHUCK:
Look, all due respect,

06:02.057 --> 06:03.624
I was at The Vatican
when she attacked it,

06:03.667 --> 06:05.669
and that place was also
considered pretty secure.

06:05.713 --> 06:07.323
You can't stop her.

06:07.367 --> 06:08.803
But while she's focused
on taking the building,

06:08.846 --> 06:10.413
we can grab the
Banner, disappear.

06:10.457 --> 06:12.589
Buy your men time
to defuse the nuke.

06:12.633 --> 06:15.766
We can help.This is the safest
place for you.

06:15.810 --> 06:18.290
As you Americans say,

06:18.334 --> 06:20.467
it is our Alamo.

06:20.510 --> 06:22.730
Uh, I don't want to be that guy,

06:22.773 --> 06:25.080
but everyone at the Alamo died.

06:25.123 --> 06:27.169
What, really?

06:27.212 --> 06:29.258
Yep.

06:34.916 --> 06:38.833
Superintendent...
are we under arrest?

06:38.876 --> 06:40.443
No, ma'am.

06:40.487 --> 06:43.359
Great, wonderful,
then we will take our leave.

06:46.493 --> 06:49.800
I must insist
you stay.

06:49.844 --> 06:53.108
I don't need an international
incident

06:53.151 --> 06:54.892
falling in my lap if
anything happens

06:54.936 --> 06:57.417
to a bunch of Westerners
on my watch.

06:57.460 --> 07:00.463
You will remain here until I
deem it safe for you to leave.

07:05.207 --> 07:07.122
We...

07:07.165 --> 07:10.473
What is Violet waiting for?

07:11.909 --> 07:14.782
Everything she's done so far
has been misdirection.

07:16.218 --> 07:17.480
Why light the signal
and give the cops

07:17.524 --> 07:18.786
time to cover the doors?

07:18.829 --> 07:21.266
SHAW:
Wait, you-you don't think

07:21.310 --> 07:23.355
she'll attack?

07:24.574 --> 07:26.968
She's not coming
through the doors.

07:28.273 --> 07:30.841
[grunting]

07:39.894 --> 07:42.026
[grunting continues]

07:47.249 --> 07:49.294
[grunts]

07:50.644 --> 07:53.255
Find me my Banner.

07:53.298 --> 07:55.953
[grunts]

07:55.997 --> 07:58.782
And kill anything that moves.

08:04.396 --> 08:07.312
[distant shouting, gunfire]

08:12.056 --> 08:13.971
I couldn't help but
notice it doesn't sound

08:14.015 --> 08:15.756
like things are going
particularly well down there.

08:15.799 --> 08:18.802
Shut up.You listen to me,
Superintendent, please!

08:18.846 --> 08:20.674
At this moment in time,

08:20.717 --> 08:24.155
everybody in the world believes
that I am the Great Khan.

08:24.199 --> 08:25.809
And that's exactly
the way she wants it.

08:25.853 --> 08:27.332
Which means she's gonna kill

08:27.376 --> 08:29.073
everyone in this police station,
including you.

08:29.117 --> 08:31.423
The most important thing is
she leaves no witnesses.

08:31.467 --> 08:33.251
So we need to run,
Superintendent.

08:33.295 --> 08:35.340
We need to get out of here!

08:37.212 --> 08:39.301
Listen.

08:39.344 --> 08:41.085
She's outnumbered.

08:41.129 --> 08:44.219
And we don't run.

08:44.262 --> 08:46.090
Then we're just fish
in a barrel.

08:46.134 --> 08:48.223
We need to get the hell
out of this room.

08:48.266 --> 08:50.007
Nah, we need to get
the hell out of this city.

08:51.618 --> 08:53.184
Yeah, I said it.

08:53.228 --> 08:54.664
I was all for saving the day,

08:54.708 --> 08:56.144
but now it's time
to pull the rip cord.

08:56.187 --> 08:57.493
As always, Shaw,
you can run if you want to.

08:57.537 --> 08:58.799
I'm going after the Banner.

08:58.842 --> 09:00.888
I'll save Simon.Save Simon?

09:00.931 --> 09:02.629
Yeah, Violet's gonna murder him.

09:02.672 --> 09:04.587
Also, he said he knows
all of Violet's plan.

09:04.631 --> 09:06.589
If she gets
the Banner first,

09:06.633 --> 09:08.635
we'll need to know how she plans
to get out of the city.

09:08.678 --> 09:10.375
Fair, I'll hot-wire this thing.

09:13.161 --> 09:15.424
You know what?

09:15.467 --> 09:18.035
I don't think
you need to bother.

09:33.877 --> 09:35.662
Stairs.FATHER CHUCK:Wait.

09:35.705 --> 09:38.012
How are we gonna avoid getting
killed by all those ninjas?

09:38.055 --> 09:41.102
Which is apparently
a sentence I say now.

09:41.145 --> 09:43.974
[distant gunfire continues]

09:44.018 --> 09:46.977
The armory's
right above us.

09:49.850 --> 09:51.678
Time to regulate.

09:51.721 --> 09:54.463
[chuckles]
I'm regulated, thanks.

09:54.506 --> 09:56.204
Mm, you sure?

09:56.247 --> 09:58.032
I'm good.

09:59.424 --> 10:01.731
I'll just hold onto it.

10:01.775 --> 10:03.254
In case you change your mind.

10:08.216 --> 10:10.000
Well...

10:10.044 --> 10:11.959
looks like it's up
to just us again.

10:12.002 --> 10:14.570
As per usual.

10:14.614 --> 10:16.790
Maybe Shaw's right.

10:16.833 --> 10:19.619
When you guys get Simon,
get the hell out of Hong Kong

10:19.662 --> 10:21.969
as soon as possible;
I'll meet you with the Banner.

10:22.012 --> 10:24.101
I'm not leaving the city
without you.

10:27.496 --> 10:29.367
Let's meet up outside
the bullpen, yeah?

10:29.411 --> 10:31.587
SHAW:
Hey...

10:31.631 --> 10:33.502
I'll make sure
you get to the Banner.

10:33.545 --> 10:35.243
Thanks.

10:35.286 --> 10:36.853
And, Danny,
I'll help you find Simon.

10:36.897 --> 10:39.682
I got your back...
and a direct line to God.

10:39.726 --> 10:42.337
Good, we can use
all the help we can get.

10:42.380 --> 10:44.252
Let's go.

10:48.822 --> 10:51.738
[gunfire continues]

10:51.781 --> 10:53.783
[glass shatters]

10:53.827 --> 10:56.351
[gunfire nearby]

10:56.394 --> 10:58.266
[canister rolling, gas hissing]

10:58.309 --> 11:00.616
I need this table.

11:00.660 --> 11:04.272
Don't do anything stupid and
we'll all get out of this alive.

11:20.636 --> 11:22.943
[officers grunting]

11:49.752 --> 11:51.754
♪

11:55.889 --> 11:58.543
[grunting]

12:09.772 --> 12:11.774
[grunting]

12:37.669 --> 12:39.584
[clucks tongue]

12:50.291 --> 12:52.206
Open it.

13:18.754 --> 13:20.800
♪

13:40.907 --> 13:42.952
♪

13:52.048 --> 13:54.442
[lock clunking]

14:05.757 --> 14:07.890
VIOLET:
It's gone.

14:07.934 --> 14:10.501
Where is it?
Where's the Banner?

14:10.545 --> 14:12.112
[shouts]

14:19.162 --> 14:21.861
I'm done playing games, Lexi!

14:21.904 --> 14:24.124
Bring me the Banner,

14:24.167 --> 14:26.517
or I'll kill everyone
in this city!

14:32.610 --> 14:34.569
Spread out,
they couldn't have gotten far.

14:44.753 --> 14:46.363
[radio crackling]

14:46.407 --> 14:48.104
HARDWICK: Lexi doesn't have
your precious Banner,

14:48.148 --> 14:50.367
Violet, I do.

14:50.411 --> 14:52.761
Remember me?

14:52.804 --> 14:55.068
Meet me in the bullpen.

14:55.111 --> 14:56.896
With me.

15:15.871 --> 15:17.917
♪

15:20.441 --> 15:22.269
Simon?

15:22.312 --> 15:24.401
Where are you?

15:24.445 --> 15:26.926
HARDWICK: We have
so much to discuss, Violet.

15:26.969 --> 15:29.972
VIOLET:
Tell me where you are.

15:30.016 --> 15:32.627
I'm happy to meet up.

15:34.672 --> 15:37.240
Yeah, I'm-I'm not sure
that's such a smart idea.

15:37.284 --> 15:39.547
Not that I'm playing hard
to get.

15:39.590 --> 15:42.202
Well, I am a bit with you,
if I'm honest.

15:42.245 --> 15:44.987
'Cause I think if you got hold
of me, you'd torture me

15:45.031 --> 15:46.989
until I told you
where I hid the Banner.

15:47.033 --> 15:50.166
And I, I've got other plans
tonight, quite frankly.

15:50.210 --> 15:52.516
Right at this very minute,

15:52.560 --> 15:55.345
I expect you are directing
your strike team to find me.

15:59.045 --> 16:01.003
Whoa, whoa, whoa!Hey!

16:01.047 --> 16:02.918
So what do you reckon
Simon's game is?

16:02.962 --> 16:04.093
He can't think Violet's
gonna make any deal

16:04.137 --> 16:05.573
with him that lets him live.

16:05.616 --> 16:08.532
Regardless, the Banner's
still in here somewhere.

16:11.057 --> 16:13.059
He's trying to buy us
time to find it.

16:13.102 --> 16:15.148
But if Violet does get
to the Banner first, Shaw,

16:15.191 --> 16:17.367
you know how to disarm a nuke?

16:17.411 --> 16:19.674
Hell no, I've never dealt
with nukes before.

16:23.983 --> 16:25.854
But seeing as how everyone
we've told about it

16:25.897 --> 16:27.943
is now dead,
I-I think I can take a look.

16:27.987 --> 16:29.901
FATHER CHUCK:
Yeah, uh, I'll help you out.

16:29.945 --> 16:31.512
You could use
an extra pair of hands.

16:31.555 --> 16:33.557
Yeah, and if not,
I'll definitely need a priest.

16:33.601 --> 16:35.516
LEXI: See ya back.Good luck.

16:35.559 --> 16:36.517
You, too.

16:36.560 --> 16:38.432
Awesome.

16:38.475 --> 16:40.608
Two brilliant psychopaths

16:40.651 --> 16:42.305
playing a game of chess
for a trillion dollars,

16:42.349 --> 16:44.699
and if one of them wins,
a city full of people blows up.

16:49.095 --> 16:50.618
I considered running.

16:50.661 --> 16:53.012
Then I realized
the Great Khan would be able

16:53.055 --> 16:54.796
to find me anywhere
in the world.

16:54.839 --> 16:56.493
You're damn right, I can.

16:56.537 --> 16:58.321
And then I'd have the
authorities and the whole

16:58.365 --> 17:00.454
of the criminal underworld on
my case for the rest of my life.

17:00.497 --> 17:02.369
That's a heavy thought,
isn't it?

17:02.412 --> 17:04.240
Just tell me
where the Banner is, Simon.

17:04.284 --> 17:06.634
With all that money,
we could buy our own country

17:06.677 --> 17:08.766
with no extradition laws.

17:08.810 --> 17:11.465
Face it, Simon.

17:11.508 --> 17:14.337
The only way
you stay free is with me.

17:14.381 --> 17:17.340
You make a compelling argument,
but you remember that last time

17:17.384 --> 17:19.168
where you got me
to take the fall for you.

17:19.212 --> 17:21.388
I remember it like it was
just a couple of hours ago.

17:21.431 --> 17:23.172
Because it was.

17:23.216 --> 17:26.088
There should be a staircase
over here that leads us out.

17:28.569 --> 17:29.613
Oh, perfect.

17:29.657 --> 17:31.441
[all grunting]

17:31.485 --> 17:34.053
Shaw!Get out of here, Chuck. Go!

17:34.096 --> 17:36.055
I don't know where I'm going!

17:36.098 --> 17:37.447
Get to White Chapel!

17:37.491 --> 17:39.536
[shouts]

17:41.321 --> 17:44.672
Okay, now you did it.
Now I'm angry!

17:47.544 --> 17:49.372
HARDWICK:
I mean, I was pretty sure

17:49.416 --> 17:51.418
that something was up
at the very beginning.

17:51.461 --> 17:54.377
But to be honest, I was just
happy to be out of prison.

17:54.421 --> 17:56.423
But your mistake was believing

17:56.466 --> 17:58.077
that you could pull one
over on me.

17:58.120 --> 18:00.383
And frankly, I'm a little
surprised that you thought

18:00.427 --> 18:03.125
I'd buy into
all of your nonsense.Okay, I didn't expect that.

18:03.169 --> 18:06.215
You were after all, dealing with
one of the greatest criminal...

18:06.259 --> 18:08.304
He could've already
left the building.

18:08.348 --> 18:10.828
He could get out,
set the bomb off himself,

18:10.872 --> 18:12.352
disappear forever.

18:12.395 --> 18:14.832
He wouldn't do that.
Would he?

18:14.876 --> 18:17.226
I'm pretty comfortable expecting
the worst at this point.

18:17.270 --> 18:19.707
This keeps getting
easier and easier.

18:19.750 --> 18:22.231
HARDWICK: You were using me
to be your fall guy.

18:22.275 --> 18:26.017
But I have to say,
you chose the wrong one.

18:26.061 --> 18:28.672
What can I say, Simon?
The best way to steal

18:28.716 --> 18:31.632
$1.5 trillion is
not to let anyone know

18:31.675 --> 18:34.330
you stole $1.5 trillion.

18:34.374 --> 18:36.506
The first rule
of being a mastermind

18:36.550 --> 18:39.074
is don't tell anyone
you're a mastermind.

18:39.118 --> 18:40.467
Touché.

18:40.510 --> 18:42.599
All right, Violet,
I'll level with you.

18:42.643 --> 18:45.341
I'll tell you where
the Banner is, but not just you.

18:45.385 --> 18:46.864
Why shouldn't everyone have
a chance to be

18:46.908 --> 18:48.388
the richest person in the world?

18:48.431 --> 18:50.129
Especially when they find out
that your plan

18:50.172 --> 18:51.739
was to escape the city

18:51.782 --> 18:55.003
and watch everyone else die
in a big explosion.

18:55.046 --> 18:58.049
But that's just more collateral
damage for the Great Khan.

18:58.093 --> 19:00.530
Simon, I'm going to kill you.

19:00.574 --> 19:02.880
Well, you can try. But you're
gonna have to fight

19:02.924 --> 19:04.404
through your own army first.

19:04.447 --> 19:06.362
Which will give me a head start
to stealing

19:06.406 --> 19:08.059
your escape plan--
I'm sure that your pilot

19:08.103 --> 19:10.192
won't be too hard to bribe.

19:10.236 --> 19:12.716
What do you think? So...

19:12.760 --> 19:14.718
may the best man or woman,

19:14.762 --> 19:17.330
be they Khan
or foot soldier, win.

19:17.373 --> 19:19.723
The Banner...

19:19.767 --> 19:22.248
is on the booking desk.

19:33.476 --> 19:35.609
[shouts][gunshots]

19:48.143 --> 19:50.624
[grunting]

20:09.077 --> 20:11.906
Down![gunshots]

20:19.479 --> 20:21.568
How the tables turn, my friends.

20:23.570 --> 20:25.615
Oh, and...

20:25.659 --> 20:27.704
you're going the wrong way.

20:34.972 --> 20:37.671
I have never been happier
to be wrong.

20:37.714 --> 20:40.108
Neither have I.

20:40.151 --> 20:42.197
[sirens wailing]

20:51.337 --> 20:55.166
"Get to White Chapel,
get to White Chapel."

20:55.210 --> 20:58.169
Shaw, what are you
talking about?

21:02.435 --> 21:05.264
♪

21:18.668 --> 21:21.192
Danny?

21:21.236 --> 21:23.282
Down there.

21:29.592 --> 21:31.725
She's got the Banner.

21:37.296 --> 21:39.254
"Bond Street."

21:39.298 --> 21:41.256
"King's Road."

21:41.300 --> 21:43.998
Bond Street. King's Road.

21:44.955 --> 21:47.001
London streets.

21:48.524 --> 21:51.571
London streets.
Bond Street. King's Road.

21:53.964 --> 21:56.140
Like Whitechapel.

21:59.056 --> 22:01.581
Two rights and a left.

22:01.624 --> 22:04.410
Two rights... and a left.

22:05.411 --> 22:07.413
Two rights and a left.

22:07.456 --> 22:09.502
♪

22:25.518 --> 22:28.477
Crap. That is

22:28.521 --> 22:31.524
definitely a bomb.

22:38.879 --> 22:41.185
I don't... I don't see her.Yeah,

22:41.229 --> 22:42.883
I don't, either.

22:42.926 --> 22:44.928
She could be anywhere
by now.

22:44.972 --> 22:47.409
Look, we can't
evacuate the city.

22:47.453 --> 22:49.368
There's no way
to warn everyone.

22:49.411 --> 22:50.673
She's gonna blow up
the whole city

22:50.717 --> 22:53.197
the moment she's clear,
so what do we do?

22:53.241 --> 22:55.243
Okay.

22:56.200 --> 22:57.767
Come on.

22:58.899 --> 23:01.945
Come on, come on.
[sighs]

23:08.778 --> 23:10.737
Nothing.

23:10.780 --> 23:13.914
Course not. You're
a hundred feet below the city.

23:13.957 --> 23:16.612
All right, Simon said
something about a pilot,

23:16.656 --> 23:19.354
but the airport would be
shut down by the blackout.

23:19.398 --> 23:21.661
Okay. Okay.
This is my mess.

23:21.704 --> 23:23.706
You go.No, you can't
do this alone.

23:23.750 --> 23:26.448
Then I'll die trying.Lexi, we are done
letting her separate us.

23:26.492 --> 23:29.625
LEXI:
Wait. Helicopters.

23:30.626 --> 23:32.411
The people she served.

23:32.454 --> 23:33.890
They live in a high-rise.

23:33.934 --> 23:35.457
She called it the Queen's Tower.

23:35.501 --> 23:37.459
She always talked
about how it had a helipad.

23:37.503 --> 23:39.418
That's how she's
getting out.

23:43.857 --> 23:45.424
[exhales]

23:57.392 --> 23:59.655
[buzzes][groans]

24:01.527 --> 24:03.311
[sighs]

24:03.354 --> 24:05.052
This is a bad idea.

24:05.095 --> 24:07.446
This is a very, very bad idea.

24:19.370 --> 24:22.591
Hey, God. Um, it's me, Chuck.

24:22.635 --> 24:24.332
Donnelly.

24:24.375 --> 24:26.987
From work.

24:27.030 --> 24:29.119
You've given me a great life.

24:29.163 --> 24:30.947
Good health, great friends.

24:30.991 --> 24:33.907
The Red Sox winning
the World Series in my lifetime.

24:33.950 --> 24:36.387
Point is, um...

24:36.431 --> 24:39.129
I know we've had
some moments lately

24:39.173 --> 24:42.132
where I've questioned my calling

24:42.176 --> 24:44.221
and you,

24:44.265 --> 24:46.746
but I feel like we're
in a good place right now.

24:46.789 --> 24:51.272
We both know that I shouldn't be
the only one here.

24:52.795 --> 24:55.276
But I'm all that's left.

24:56.233 --> 24:57.887
And if this thing goes off,

24:57.931 --> 25:01.891
it'll kill seven million people,

25:01.935 --> 25:04.546
including the people I love.

25:05.547 --> 25:08.985
So I'm ready to do
whatever you need me to do.

25:11.205 --> 25:13.163
Even if it means
sacrificing myself

25:13.207 --> 25:15.252
for everybody else.

25:16.776 --> 25:18.821
Just show me the way.

25:19.822 --> 25:21.432
Please.

25:22.433 --> 25:24.479
And amen.

25:28.439 --> 25:30.485
[exhaling heavily]

25:44.891 --> 25:46.936
[phone chimes]

25:55.162 --> 25:57.338
[exhales]

26:02.038 --> 26:03.518
You got to be kidding me.

26:03.562 --> 26:05.128
VIDEO NARRATOR:
This is a nuclear weapon.

26:05.172 --> 26:07.783
Inside every
implosion-type fission device

26:07.827 --> 26:09.655
are two key components:

26:09.698 --> 26:12.048
the primary, which includes
the explosives for detonation,

26:12.092 --> 26:14.398
and the secondary,
which is made of either

26:14.442 --> 26:16.575
highly enriched uranium
or plutonium.

26:16.618 --> 26:18.707
What gives the weapon
its nuclear reaction

26:18.751 --> 26:20.709
is suspended inside the primary,

26:20.753 --> 26:24.017
easily identifiable
as it's encased in gold or lead

26:24.060 --> 26:26.759
to shield the radiation
to anyone near it.

26:26.802 --> 26:28.369
Unlike the movies,

26:28.412 --> 26:30.501
the goal of quickly dismantling
a nuclear weapon

26:30.545 --> 26:32.373
isn't cutting wires or defusion.

26:32.416 --> 26:33.983
It's disassembly.

26:34.027 --> 26:36.464
Removing the fusion fuel
of highly enriched uranium

26:36.507 --> 26:38.597
will prevent
the nuclear chain reaction

26:38.640 --> 26:40.599
and render any warhead
simply explosive,

26:40.642 --> 26:42.644
not radioactive,

26:42.688 --> 26:44.646
and therefore
decrease its blast force

26:44.690 --> 26:46.213
from citywide destruction

26:46.256 --> 26:48.694
to knocking out
a few neighborhood windows.

26:48.737 --> 26:50.565
The best way to achieve that
is simple.

26:50.609 --> 26:52.915
Here's how you...

26:52.959 --> 26:55.701
No. No, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no!

26:55.744 --> 26:57.833
No, no, no, no!

26:57.877 --> 27:00.749
[groans, exhales]

27:00.793 --> 27:02.795
Fine.

27:03.796 --> 27:05.841
I'll do it myself.

27:10.803 --> 27:13.283
How do I get this open?

27:21.465 --> 27:23.511
♪

27:25.295 --> 27:27.341
[helicopter blades whirring]

27:30.170 --> 27:31.998
[mouths]

27:44.750 --> 27:46.490
Simon!

28:01.680 --> 28:05.640
[gun clicks]Looks like you chose
the wrong fall guy.

28:07.642 --> 28:10.079
I'll find Simon eventually.

28:10.123 --> 28:12.473
I'll find everyone
who turned against me.

28:17.260 --> 28:19.436
There's nowhere to go!

28:20.437 --> 28:22.048
It's over.

28:24.659 --> 28:27.227
The whole world's
gonna know, Violet.

28:27.270 --> 28:31.666
Simon got you to admit
being the Great Khan on camera.

28:32.667 --> 28:33.668
[sighs]

28:33.712 --> 28:35.714
It's done.

28:42.764 --> 28:44.287
Not yet.

28:46.072 --> 28:47.595
[exhales]

28:48.727 --> 28:50.685
I'm getting out of here.

28:50.729 --> 28:53.688
Or I'm taking
seven million people with me.

28:54.820 --> 28:56.299
Drop your guns

28:56.343 --> 28:58.693
and kick them to me.Like hell.

29:00.086 --> 29:02.305
Danny! Do it.

29:05.178 --> 29:06.353
[gun slides]

29:06.396 --> 29:07.920
Lex.

29:19.627 --> 29:21.629
You know,
in all the excitement,

29:21.672 --> 29:23.022
you forgot your knife.

29:23.065 --> 29:24.458
[Violet grunts, gasps]

29:24.501 --> 29:26.112
[grunting]

29:36.600 --> 29:37.776
DANNY:
Ah!

29:40.822 --> 29:42.563
[all grunting]

29:46.785 --> 29:48.090
Oh!

29:50.223 --> 29:51.180
[shouts]

29:54.880 --> 29:56.185
Danny!

29:57.447 --> 29:59.319
[Violet shouts]

30:08.197 --> 30:10.504
[grunting]

30:22.211 --> 30:23.691
Is that all you got?

30:23.734 --> 30:26.476
[panting]
Great Khan.

30:36.791 --> 30:39.141
You never could beat me, Lexi.

30:39.185 --> 30:42.144
You're just mad

30:42.188 --> 30:44.581
that I chose him,

30:44.625 --> 30:46.322
not you.

30:47.758 --> 30:49.412
[grunting]

31:02.077 --> 31:04.123
DANNY:
Hey!

31:07.822 --> 31:09.563
Don't you need this?

31:13.959 --> 31:16.178
You could have gotten away,

31:16.222 --> 31:19.747
but you risked an entire city

31:19.790 --> 31:21.967
for one person.

31:22.010 --> 31:23.751
[coughing]

31:23.794 --> 31:25.753
You both make each other weak.

31:30.149 --> 31:32.238
Maybe.

31:34.153 --> 31:36.590
[detonator slides]

31:36.633 --> 31:38.809
[chuckles softly]

31:44.859 --> 31:47.209
You think
this is gonna save you?

31:47.253 --> 31:49.298
No.

31:50.691 --> 31:52.432
She will.

31:52.475 --> 31:54.129
[groans loudly]

31:54.173 --> 31:56.697
[grunts]

31:56.740 --> 31:58.655
[gasping]

32:04.835 --> 32:06.794
[grunts][clicks]

32:06.837 --> 32:08.665
[gasping]

32:08.709 --> 32:10.406
[clicking]

32:10.450 --> 32:12.495
♪

32:14.236 --> 32:17.196
[panting]

32:17.239 --> 32:19.198
Way to go, Chuckie-boy.

32:19.241 --> 32:21.330
[buzzing]

32:25.944 --> 32:27.032
[explosion]

32:28.859 --> 32:30.905
[panting]

32:32.037 --> 32:33.473
[gasps]

32:34.430 --> 32:36.476
[Lexi panting]

32:46.442 --> 32:48.531
Hey. Hang on. I got you.

32:48.575 --> 32:52.318
Shaw and Chuck, they did it.[breathing raggedly]

32:53.319 --> 32:55.060
They did it.

32:55.103 --> 32:57.584
Are you there?I knew they would.

32:57.627 --> 33:00.543
Stay with me. Stay with me.

33:03.982 --> 33:05.984
♪

33:19.432 --> 33:21.477
♪

33:24.219 --> 33:26.178
[flare gun fires]

33:26.221 --> 33:27.570
[panting]

33:27.614 --> 33:28.963
[grunts softly]

33:29.007 --> 33:30.834
Danny. Danny.

33:30.878 --> 33:32.314
Hey.

33:32.358 --> 33:34.751
Wake up. Help's on the way.

33:34.795 --> 33:38.103
[groans]Help's on the way.

33:38.146 --> 33:41.976
I'm sorry
I'm bleeding all over you.

33:42.020 --> 33:43.760
Don't be silly. We're
bleeding all over each other,

33:43.804 --> 33:45.023
just like old times.

33:45.066 --> 33:47.808
You're gonna be fine.

33:47.851 --> 33:50.028
We always find a way.I, uh...

33:51.072 --> 33:53.596
I'm not so sure about this one.

33:53.640 --> 33:55.685
Shh.

34:00.038 --> 34:01.387
I should have asked you.

34:07.045 --> 34:09.569
I would have said yes.

34:14.617 --> 34:17.577
[breathes deeply]
You know, in some cultures,

34:17.620 --> 34:20.667
when blood mixes together,

34:20.710 --> 34:24.366
the-the souls do, as well.

34:24.410 --> 34:27.456
Which means, technically,

34:27.500 --> 34:29.676
that we're one.

34:29.719 --> 34:32.331
[whispers]:
We're one.

34:34.594 --> 34:37.162
Did we just get married?[chuckles]

34:38.163 --> 34:41.122
We've never done anything else
traditionally.

34:41.166 --> 34:44.082
Why start now, don't you think?

34:45.518 --> 34:47.302
I do.

34:48.303 --> 34:50.479
[whispers]:
I do, too.

34:53.656 --> 34:55.963
[grunts]
No, no. No, no, no.

34:56.006 --> 34:58.618
No. No, you see,

34:58.661 --> 35:00.663
that's official.

35:00.707 --> 35:03.013
I'm telling you, you can't die.

35:03.057 --> 35:05.581
You can't die. Do you
understand? I'm not having it.

35:09.368 --> 35:11.761
I'm one half of you,

35:11.805 --> 35:14.764
so you have to listen to me.

35:14.808 --> 35:16.201
[exhales]

35:16.244 --> 35:19.682
The Year of the Rat.

35:19.726 --> 35:22.685
What?The son of a...

35:22.729 --> 35:26.341
Danny...Shaw was right.

35:28.735 --> 35:30.693
Convergence.

35:30.737 --> 35:32.391
Please.

35:32.434 --> 35:35.263
Stay with me. Stay with me.

35:35.307 --> 35:36.786
[grunts softly]

35:36.830 --> 35:38.179
Stay with me.[helicopter blades whirring]

35:38.223 --> 35:40.616
I love you.

35:40.660 --> 35:42.705
♪

35:45.099 --> 35:48.363
He saved the lives of millions
of people in Hong Kong.

35:48.407 --> 35:50.583
That is correct, Your Honor.

35:50.626 --> 35:52.889
Last year,
he also saved the lives

35:52.933 --> 35:55.414
of myself and several others,

35:55.457 --> 35:58.982
helping to thwart
the terrorist Karim Farouk.

35:59.026 --> 36:01.028
Simply put,

36:01.071 --> 36:02.812
Dwayne Coleman is a hero.

36:04.858 --> 36:06.816
Now, my client would
be the first to admit

36:06.860 --> 36:08.166
he's made many mistakes,

36:08.209 --> 36:12.518
broken many laws
along the way, Your Honor.

36:12.561 --> 36:17.262
And he would be the last
to admit all the good he's done.

36:17.305 --> 36:21.135
But we have a system
that believes in redemption.

36:21.179 --> 36:24.486
And if anyone
has earned a second chance,

36:24.530 --> 36:26.445
Dwayne Coleman has.

36:27.446 --> 36:30.144
I'd like to call
your attention

36:30.188 --> 36:32.364
to the written affidavit

36:32.407 --> 36:36.455
and character testimony
of CIA Agent Kathryn Reece,

36:36.498 --> 36:39.588
killed in service

36:39.632 --> 36:41.242
only a day after she filed it.

36:41.286 --> 36:43.070
You'll also find
a statement

36:43.113 --> 36:44.985
from Bishop Charles Donnelly.

36:52.297 --> 36:56.083
Well, as it's, uh,
my understanding

36:56.126 --> 36:58.781
that the government agrees
with this position,

36:58.825 --> 37:00.566
I'm, uh...

37:00.609 --> 37:04.222
I'm happy
to accept the plea deal

37:04.265 --> 37:06.702
and, uh, extend

37:06.746 --> 37:10.489
a sincere
"welcome home, Mr. Coleman."

37:10.532 --> 37:11.490
[cheering, applause]

37:11.533 --> 37:13.448
[whooping][Danny chuckles]

37:13.492 --> 37:16.059
Ah.
[chuckles]

37:16.103 --> 37:17.496
Thank you.

37:17.539 --> 37:19.498
Least I can do.

37:19.541 --> 37:22.065
Hey.Ah!

37:22.109 --> 37:25.112
[laughs]
Oh, it's good to see you.

37:25.155 --> 37:28.028
MAN:
Good to see you, too, man.[Shaw laughs]

37:28.071 --> 37:30.726
Aw.
[laughs]

37:30.770 --> 37:33.207
Hey, baby girl.
[chuckles]

37:33.251 --> 37:34.817
You don't remember
me, do you?

37:34.861 --> 37:37.864
I'm your Uncle Dwayne.
Get in here.

37:37.907 --> 37:40.040
Yes. Oh, bro...

37:40.997 --> 37:43.478
Dwayne's back.Dwayne's back.

37:43.522 --> 37:45.306
[all laugh]

37:45.350 --> 37:47.265
Let's go home.

37:49.310 --> 37:51.181
[chuckles]

37:53.140 --> 37:56.186
We heard the cheering
from up here.

37:57.318 --> 38:00.060
Well done, Counselor.Well,

38:00.103 --> 38:01.714
I haven't been in front
of a judge in a while,

38:01.757 --> 38:04.717
but even I
couldn't screw this one up.Mm.

38:04.760 --> 38:07.067
[footsteps approach]LAWYER:
Bishop Donnelly?

38:08.677 --> 38:12.638
Yeah. That's me.I'm the executor
of the Reece estate.

38:12.681 --> 38:14.640
Kathryn Reece

38:14.683 --> 38:17.120
updated her CIA file
just before passing,

38:17.164 --> 38:19.601
and, well, at her request,

38:19.645 --> 38:21.473
in the event of her death...

38:22.474 --> 38:24.954
...she had wanted
you to receive this.

38:26.652 --> 38:29.350
This is the family copy
of Agent Reece's star

38:29.394 --> 38:31.831
on the Memorial
Wall of the CIA.

38:36.966 --> 38:39.969
She, uh, she has other family.

38:40.013 --> 38:42.929
She felt you
deserved it more.

38:42.972 --> 38:44.583
[whispers]:
Hey.

38:44.626 --> 38:47.586
You're Danny McNamara, yes?

38:47.629 --> 38:49.936
Kate left me something?

38:49.979 --> 38:52.808
No. Jacob Reece III did.

38:54.157 --> 38:55.637
Must have forgotten
to update his will

38:55.681 --> 38:57.552
after you put him away.

38:57.596 --> 38:59.902
Mr. Reece added you as
the primary beneficiary

38:59.946 --> 39:02.078
afterhis arrest.

39:02.122 --> 39:04.298
Many of the Reece holdings, they
will be tied up in litigation

39:04.342 --> 39:05.821
for years, but the trust

39:05.865 --> 39:08.041
is unencumbered.Oh.

39:08.084 --> 39:11.392
I'm his old, you know,
ball and chain.

39:11.436 --> 39:12.785
It goes...

39:12.828 --> 39:15.831
Oh, my God,
that's a lot of money.

39:15.875 --> 39:18.007
[whistles]Should you have any
other questions,

39:18.051 --> 39:20.575
here's my card.

39:20.619 --> 39:23.665
[chuckles softly]
Wow.

39:27.060 --> 39:29.497
Trying to buy his way
out of hell, I presume.

39:29.541 --> 39:31.151
You know, I am past

39:31.194 --> 39:34.850
trying to understand
the mind of Jacob Reece.

39:35.851 --> 39:38.245
Maybe I will talk
to this guy more.

39:38.288 --> 39:40.029
He probably has a lot
of experience with prenups.

39:41.030 --> 39:43.206
We're already married.I don't know.

39:43.250 --> 39:45.339
These guys, they work
miracles. They really do.It's not funny.

39:45.383 --> 39:47.167
It's pretty funny.Oh, it's not funny.

39:47.210 --> 39:48.516
Chuck, I need you to weigh in
on this one over here, man.

39:48.560 --> 39:50.388
